📽 @mikewolfel

node.text:
The beauty of the Faroe Islands 🤍 We can post your photos in our account, follow the link in our bio: @nomadfervor and we will select your pictures

The Faroe Islands are made up of 18 islands located about 200 miles north-northwest of Scotland and about halfway between Norway & Iceland.  The islands are rugged and rocky with some low peaks; the coasts are mostly cliffs. 

Do you think you'd be interested in visiting? 🇫🇴 

Photos & videos by:
1. @dope4travel 
2. @golden_heart 
3. @patheight
